    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending is accepted as credible for the stated COU. Quantitative validation metrics satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds across all three QoIs and all 11 test constructs. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, Gradation 2 vs. required 3) is noted; the assessment team determined that the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol provides sufficient coverage for the regulatory submission context and that residual uncertainty is bounded by the quantitative comparison results.",
